1.	Learn Section 6: OOP Part 1 and Section 7: OOP Part 2
2.	Do all Coding Exercises that you will find in Sections 6 and 7.
3.	After that complete the following tasks:

(Deadline is tomorrow midday)

1. Create a class called DateTime that includes the following information as instance variables — month, day, year, hours, minutes, seconds. 
Your class should have a constructor that initializes the instances variables and assumes that the values provided are correct. 
Provide setter and getter method for each instance variable. 
Provide a method displayDate() that displays the date format "dd/mm/yyyy".
Provide a method displayTime() that displays the time format "HH:mm:ss".
Provide a method toString() that display date and time using specified formats.
Provide a static method getCurrentDateTime() that will use System.currentTimeMillis() method to calculate current date and current time and return and object of type DateTime.
Write a test application named DateTest that demonstrates class DateTime capabilities.

2. Create a class called Employee that includes the following information as instance variables - first name, last name, age , monthly salary.
Your class should have another constructor that initializes the instances variables and assumes that the values provided are correct.
If the monthly salary is not positive, set it to 0.0.
Provide a method toString() that display employee information: "Full Name: ? Age: ? Monthly Salary: ?".
Provide a method haveSameAgeAndSalary(another_employee) that will return True if comparing 2 employees they have same age and salary.
Create two Employee objects and display each object’s yearly salary.
Then give each Employee a 10% raise and display each Employee’s yearly salary again.
Compare two employees and display comparison result.
Create a list that will contains 10 Employees.
From current list of employees find employees with minimal and maximal monthly salary and display employee information.
From current list of employees calculate the average age of employees.

3. Create a super class called Car. The Car class has the following fields and methods
- speed
- color
- realPrice
- getSalePrice()
- toString()
Create a sub class of Car class and name it as Truck. The Truck class should have the following fields and methods:
- weight
- getSalePrice() // if weight > 2000, 20% discount otherwise 10% discount
Create a subclass of Car class and name it as Ford. The Ford class has the following fields and methods:
- year
- manufacturerDiscount
- getSalePrice() // from the sale price substract manufacturerDiscount
Create a subclass of Car class and name it as Sedan. The Sedan class has the following fields and methods:
- length
- getSalePrice() // if length > 4 meters, 5% discount otherwise 10% discount
Create AutoShop class which contains the main() method.
Create a list of cars and add to the list min 2 objects of each car type.
For each car type in the list display sale price and car description (the description should include all the information about the car).
